{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012WhEbc7prSyiDqx9WiR1XY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture:\n- Current verbosity: 1 → need to increase to 2\n- Current slowOpThresholdMs: 200 → need to 2x to 400\n- Current journalCompressor: zlib → need to switch to zstd\n\nThe WiredTiger `journalCompressor` setting requires a restart (it's a storage engine option). The verbosity and slowOpThreshold can be changed at runtime, but since we need to update the configmap as the persistent config (and restart pods to pick up the WiredTiger change), I need to:\n1. Apply verbosity and slowOpThreshold changes at runtime via `db.adminCommand({setParameter: 1, ...})` to all members first to keep data available\n2. Update the configmap with all three changes\n3. Do a rolling restart of the StatefulSet, starting with secondaries then the primary, to pick up the WiredTiger change\n\nFor StatefulSets with RollingUpdate strategy, pods restart in reverse ordinal order (pod-2, pod-1, pod-0), so the primary gets restarted last, which is ideal. But I should first verify which pod is actually the primary before proceeding.\n\nSince WiredTiger journalCompressor is a startup-time setting, I'll need to apply runtime changes to verbosity and slowOpThreshold first, then update the configmap with all three settings and trigger a rolling restart. The default StatefulSet rolling update should maintain replica set health by waiting for each pod to be ready before moving to the next one.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1096,"cache_read_input_tokens":32401,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1096},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f95b620b-